# Grid theme login horizon fix

## Work Done

- Investigated a visual bug where the grid theme's glowing horizon beam (`app-main::after`) cuts across the login card.
- Traced root cause to `grid.css` lines 93–117: a fixed-position 2px `::after` pseudo-element at `top: 40vh` with a glowing cyan gradient.
- Added override in `login.css` to hide both the horizon beam and grid floor pseudo-elements when `.login-page` is present inside `.app-main`, using `:has()` scoping.

